minikube version
minikube start (start a cluser)
minikube ip
minikube service <service name>
minikube delete

kubectl version
kubectl cluster-info
kubectl get nodes
kubectl get pods
kubeclt get services
kubeclt get deployments

Create a new deployment
kubectl create deployment <name> --image=<image name>

Proxy to forward communication to cluster private network
kubectl proxy

For example, HTTP endpoints like this:
curl http://localhost:8001/version
curl http://localhost:8001/api/v1/namespaces/default/pods/<pod name>/

kubectl describe pods

Anything application normally sends to STDOUT is logged
kubectl logs <pod name>

Can execute commands as well such as
kubectl exec $POD_NAME -- env
kubectl exec -it $POD_NAME -- bash (interactive TTY session:)

kubectl describe services/<service name>

Create a new service
kubectl expose deployment/kubernetes-bootcamp --type="NodePort" --port 8080
kubectl describe deployment

Apply a new label:
kubectl label pods <pod name> version=v1
